servings: 2
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}(thinly sliced). Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%oz} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces).

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain and return cavatappi to pot.

While cavatappi cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and mushrooms; cook, undisturbed, until slightly softened and browned, ~{2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid. Add chicken to pan with veggies. (TIP: If pan seems dry, add a drizzle of oil.) Season with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender and chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir diced tomato, @tomato paste{1%unit}, and 1/3 cup water into pan with chicken and veggies. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper. TIP: If stew seems too thick, add more water a splash at a time.

Toss drained cavatappi with @butter{3%tbsp} until melted. Taste and season with salt. Divide buttered noodles between shallow bowls. Top with stew and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.